# Git workflow — kitchen library

- **Default agent flow:** See [ship-after-change.mdc](ship-after-change.mdc) — test → commit if clean → push unless the user opts out.
- For **larger features**, prefer a **feature branch** (e.g. `improvement/short-description`), then merge to `main` after checks. Small fixes on `main` are fine for this personal site.
- After meaningful UI changes, **verify in a browser** (static server from repo root): affected pages load, modals work, search/order list as relevant.
- Use **Conventional Commits**: `feat(html):`, `fix(riviera):`, `chore(cursor):`, `docs:`.
- **Commit often** with small, logical messages; **push regularly** so GitHub / Pages stay current.
